laboratory_examinations.findings: Patent ductus arteriosus and a moderate atrial septal defect.
Mild to moderate laryngomalacia and a deep inter-arytenoid groove with salivary pooling.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brain
laboratory_examinations.findings: Incidental finding of a prominent left frontal developmental venous anomaly.
Identification of two variants in the PLXND1 gene: one synonymous, likely benign (LBEN) variant, and one missense variant of uncertain significance (VUS).
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Familial analysis confirmed the variant to be maternally inherited.
